Used Aimpoint CompM2 Red Dot Optic. Great condition, fresh set of batteries.  The CompM2 is a battery-powered, non-magnifying red dot type of reflex sight for firearms manufactured byAimpoint AB. It was first introduced in the U.S. Armed Forces in 2000, designated as the M68 Close Combat Optic (M68 CCO). It is also known as theM68 Aimpoint and is designed to meet United States military standards. The sight is designed for use with the M16/M4 family of rifles, but can be mounted on any weapon fitted with an upper Picatinny rail. It is also NVG-compatible—the aiming dot is still visible through night vision scopes and goggles.
Formally used by the United States Military, the Aimpoint CompM2 is built for extreme conditions. These sights have a special hard-anodized surface and are waterproof to a depth of 75 ft.
